post_text: Parents - Completing this speed test at your house on multiple devices will help our district and the Georgia Department of Education know what kind of internet access our families have.
shared_text:
Georgia Department of Education
June 23 at 7:41 PM ·

Governor Kemp announced today that the Georgia Broadband Deployment Initiative (GBDI) is launching the Speedtest by Ookla® pilot project statewide through August. This project is designed to equip school leaders with the clearest picture possible of internet connectivity for Georgia’s students and teachers for the upcoming school year.

Georgians are encouraged to download the free Ookla Speedtest app (Android or iOS-Apple) to the various devices that they use to connect to the internet (smartphones, tablets, laptops, and desktop computers) and take several tests in the places where connectivity is important to them. The easy-to-use Speedtest, along with the information available at the Broadband Initiative website, will assist school leaders as they plan for their digital learning strategies.

Click here for more information: https://gov.georgia.gov/press-releases/2020-06-23/state-launches-internet-speedtest-pilot-schools

post_text:
The University of Georgia K-12 Reading Program has opened early, reduced rates, and converted all classes to a live online format, to help parents and schools maintain student education during these unusual times.

Our live, teacher-led online classes are available now and throughout the summer, for Pre-K through 12th grade students.

The curriculum is high caliber and has been taught in a live, online format for 5 years already with over 50,000 school-age students. The classes are led by highly-trained teachers with many years’ experience teaching effectively in online classrooms. Skills taught include:

Early Elementary: letter recognition, phonemic awareness, sight words, phonics
Mid-to-Late Elementary: fluency, phonics, long-word decoding, comprehension, textbook reading, writing
Middle and High School: doubling reading speed, comprehension, writing, notetaking, test preparation, textbook strategies

https://uga.readingclasses.org/

Cook County Family Connection is offering a Free Food Drop specifically for Baby Hornet families. The drive-through event will begin at 1:00 pm this Thursday (April 16) at the Multi-Purpose Facility building (303 South College Street) in Sparks. Georgia Department of Education
April 1 at 5:43 PM ·

NEWS:

In his press conference this afternoon, Governor Brian Kemp announced that Georgia's K-12 public schools will remain closed for in-person instruction for the remainder of the school year. Essential functions (including school meals and distance learning) can continue.

We appreciate the teachers and parents who have worked so hard throughout this transition. This extended period of distance learning is brand-new for our state and our nation, but Georgia's students are in good hands as we work together to keep them safe and keep them learning.

Cook County Families: The Georgia Department of Education is offering a free webinar (Talking To and Supporting Our Children During the Pandemic).
We invite parents and others caring for children during the pandemic to join a webinar this Thursday, April 2nd at 2:00 p.m., as Dr. David Schonfeld joins us live to provide the presentation “Talking to and Supporting our Children during the Pandemic.” He will be available to answer questions, also. Dr. Schonfeld is a developmental-behavioral pediatrician and the Director of the National Center for School Crisis and Bereavement at Children’s Hospital Los Angeles, as well as Professor of Clinical Pediatrics at the Keck School of Medicine, University of Southern California. He is a member the Executive Committee of the American Academy of Pediatrics Council on Disaster Preparedness and Recovery and he serves on the National Biodefense Science Board.
If you're interested click this link to register: https://register.gotowebinar.com/register/8101386797317232139

post_text:
Visit Waterford.org at <https://www.waterford.org/resources/story-time-videos-for-kids/> to find 30 storytime videos for young learners! Here's what you'll find:

With many schools moving online and libraries across the country closed, your children may be feeling a deep story-time void in their lives. Luckily, there are plenty of read-aloud videos available online for both picture books and chapter books. And many of them are by the book’s author or by children’s celebrities (such as Josh Gad, who voices Olaf in Disney’s Frozen).

If you’re looking for a way to keep your children reading and learning, check out our list of 30 of the best storytime videos—many of which were created in response to the COVID-19 crisis. Teachers, these can also be excellent resources to keep class story time going with your students or families while you can’t meet in person.

VALENTINE’S DAY DELIVERIES AT COOK MIDDLE SCHOOL:

Valentines deliveries will be accepted until 1:00 p.m. on Thursday, February 13th. Please keep in mind that this is an instructional day. Deliveries will be held and given to the students in the afternoon.

Students receiving balloons or glass containers will not be able to ride the bus. Please plan ahead for alternate transportation and remember all transportation changes must be made in writing.

Cook County Schools will release early today due to inclement weather. Schools will release at the following times:
CPS- 1:00 p.m.
CES- 1:00 p.m.
CMS- 1:00 p.m.
CHS- 2:00 p.m.

It is our intention to have all buses off the roads by 4:00 p.m.

We anticipate schools to open tomorrow at regular time.
